        <abstract> 
<p>Has sold 400 copies of <hi rend="italic">Facts and arguments for Darwin</hi>. It is a poor time for bookselling.</p>  
<p>Last <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Review</hi> has best exposition of Darwinism he has met with [A. R. Wallace, "Geological climates, and origin of species", <hi rend="italic">Q. Rev.</hi> 126 (1869): 359–94].</p>  
<p>Proposes to print 2000 copies of a new [5th] edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
